            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Still",
                "url": "/topics/still"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675649",
        "quote": "Precisely because white denial has long trumped claims of racism, people of color tend to underreport their experiences with racial bias rather than exaggerate them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675649"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Racism",
                "url": "/topics/racism"
            },
            {
                "name": "Color",
                "url": "/topics/color"
            },
            {
                "name": "Denial",
                "url": "/topics/denial"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675650",
        "quote": "In short, and let us be clear on it: race is not a card. It determines whom the dealer is, and who gets dealt.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675650"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Race",
                "url": "/topics/race"
            },
            {
                "name": "Let Us",
                "url": "/topics/let_us"
            },
            {
                "name": "Determines",
                "url": "/topics/determines"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675646",
        "quote": "If we don't figure out a way to create equity, real equity, of opportunity and access, to good schools, housing, health care, and decent paying jobs, we're not going to survive as a productive and healthy society.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675646"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Housing",
                "url": "/topics/housing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Decent",
                "url": "/topics/decent"
            },
            {
                "name": "Access",
                "url": "/topics/access"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675656",
        "quote": "There are lots of research, of course, saying that a vast majority of us have been exposed to racial biases and stereotypes and, to some extent, we've internalized them, because that's so ubiquitous. That's why I'm so bored with the conversation about who's a racist and who's not.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675656"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Ubiquitous",
                "url": "/topics/ubiquitous"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Extent",
                "url": "/topics/extent"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675653",
        "quote": "Sadly, whites are rarely open to what black and brown folks have to say regarding their ongoing experiences with racist mistreatment. And we are especially reluctant to discuss what that mistreatment means for us as whites: namely that we end up with more and better opportunities as the flipside of discrimination.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675653"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "End",
                "url": "/topics/end"
            },
            {
                "name": "Whites",
                "url": "/topics/whites"
            },
            {
                "name": "Ongoing",
                "url": "/topics/ongoing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675635",
        "quote": "When you allow racial disparity and institutional inequity to affect one part of the country, eventually it's coming back to get everyone.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675635"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Country",
                "url": "/topics/country"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everyone",
                "url": "/topics/everyone"
            },
            {
                "name": "Allow",
                "url": "/topics/allow"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675647",
        "quote": "For people of color - especially African Americans - the idea that racist cops might frame members of their community is no abstract notion, let alone an exercise in irrational conspiracy theorizing. Rather, it speaks to a social reality about which blacks are acutely aware.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675647"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "African Americans",
                "url": "/topics/african_americans"
            },
            {
                "name": "Cops",
                "url": "/topics/cops"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675645",
        "quote": "Violating the 4th Amendment guarantees against illegal searches and seizures is not the way to solve crime problems.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675645"
