            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675654",
        "quote": "Our failure as a society to properly acknowledge and confront the psychological, social, and political effects of white privilege has perpetuated racial inequality and race-based political resentments.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675654"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Social",
                "url": "/topics/social"
            },
            {
                "name": "Psychological",
                "url": "/topics/psychological"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675639",
        "quote": "Here's the reality. The image of a white Jesus has been used to justify enslavement, conquest, colonialism, the genocide of indigenous peoples. There are literally millions of human beings whose lives have been snuffed out by people who conquered under the banner of a white god.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_675639"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Here",
                "url": "/topics/here"
            },
            {
                "name": "Conquered",
                "url": "/topics/conquered"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_538236",
        "quote": "Being asked to describe what 'post-racial' means is a bit like being asked to describe a leprechaun, cold fusion or unicorns: we know what is meant, but, if we are willing to be honest, we also know that none of the four describe something real, something tangible, something true.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_538236"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Cold",
                "url": "/topics/cold"
            },
            {
                "name": "Willing",
                "url": "/topics/willing"
            },
            {
                "name": "None",
                "url": "/topics/none"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_538237",
        "quote": "To believe that the United States is post-racial requires an almost incomprehensible inability or unwillingness to stare truth in the face.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tim Wise",
            "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_538237"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "United States",
                "url": "/topics/united_states"
            },
            {
                "name": "Inability",
                "url": "/topics/inability"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tim_wise_538238",
        "quote": "It's hard to say when or if we will actually arrive at that place called 'post-racial', or, better yet, post-racism.",
